==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Newt
<hw>Newt</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE. <ets>ewt</ets>,
<ets>evete</ets>, AS. <ets>efete</ets>, with <ets>n</ets> prefixed,
<ets>an ewt</ets> being understood as <ets>a newt</ets>. Cf.
<er>Eft</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Any one of several species
of small aquatic salamanders. The common British species are the crested
newt (<spn>Triton cristatus</spn>) and the smooth newt (<spn>Lophinus
punctatus</spn>). In America, <spn>Diemictylus viridescens</spn> is one
of the most abundant species.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>New Thought</ent>⟦br⟧
